  <scopecontent id="aspace_c42cd09b6606267216d43087574c2b35">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>"The White Collection of Historical Medallions, including, among other things, all the casts of Eichler of Berlin, namely two thousand copies of antique gems in the Royal Museum at Berlin, illustrative of ancient history and art; over five hundred casts illustrating mediaeval and renaissance history and art; some four hundred medallion portraits of eminent personages in modern history, derived from authentic portraits." Cornell University Register, 1868-69.</p>  </scopecontent>
